Weidmann Lacks Experience to Lead Bundesbank, Welteke Tells FTD

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-02-17T20:31:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/weidmann-lacks-experience-to-lead-bundesbank-welteke-tells-ftd.html
Jens Weidmann, who is to take over
as Bundesbank president from May 1, lacks experience in leading
large organizations with many employees, former Bundesbank
President Ernst Welteke said, Financial Times Deutschland
reported, citing an interview.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
